data.description: Home is always clean and orderly.  Seller has her own cleaning business and treats her home like she does her customer’s homes.  Historic home was once a part of the railroad station as the water depot for steam locomotives traveling thru HR.  House is on HR Comm Water Asso $18.21/mo.  Living room, dining room & bedroom have sky lights.  Wood burning Earth stove heats the whole house or you can use the propane wall heat with new thermostat.  Cooling is with window unit swamp cooler and window A/C units in 2 bedrooms.  Features include formal dining room, oak wood flooring in the living room and dining room,  stainless steel appliances, eat in kitchen, deck off back of house, outside access in the backyard to cellar , metal roof, chain link totally fenced.  Yard is nicely landscaped w/rose bushes, wisteria, grape vines, and fruit trees.
